Note:
Runa Standard Library: Network Utilities

Provides comprehensive network operations including socket programming, HTTP client/server capabilities, network protocols, and advanced networking utilities.

Idiomatic Runa code uses natural language operators:
  Let socket be create socket with type as "tcp"
  Let connection be connect socket to "localhost" on port 8080
  Let response be send request to "http://api.example.com" with method as "GET"
  Let server be start server on port 3000

For advanced/AI-generated code, use helpers:
  Let result be create with type as socket_type and family as address_family
  Let result be send with socket as sock and data as message
:End Note

